<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<xsl:stylesheet version="1.1"
	xmlns:xsl="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Transform" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format"
	exclude-result-prefixes="fo" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions"
	xmlns:java="java">

	<xsl:template match="/" name="HOTLINENOTICELW">


		<fo:block-container border-color="black"
			border-style="solid" border-width="2pt" height="26cm" width="19cm">


			<fo:block margin-top="4cm" font-weight="bold" text-align="center"
				font-size="16px">
				IMPORTANT POLICYHOLDER NOTICE
			</fo:block>

			<fo:block margin-top="2cm" margin-left="2cm" margin-right="2cm"
				font-size="13px">
				As part of our value-added services
				to our Lawyers Professional
				Liability clients, Protexure now
				offers you a pre-claim and risk
				mitigation consultation “Hotline”
				staffed by independent attorneys
				that specialize in the defense
				of lawyer professional liability
				claims.
			</fo:block>

			<fo:block margin-top="2cm" margin-left="2cm" margin-right="2cm"
				font-size="13px">
				This “hotline” provides you access
				to seek advice prior to submitting a claim, or reporting of a
				circumstance that could give rise to a claim. It will also serve
				as a resource to reduce the professional liability risks inherent
				in your day-to-day practice of law. Consultation with a “Hotline”
				attorney is on a confidential basis and can serve to properly
				manage any circumstance that may lead to a potential claim.
			</fo:block>


			<fo:block margin-top="2cm" margin-left="2cm" margin-right="2cm"
				font-size="13px">
				Please call our dedicated toll free
				number Monday – Friday, between 8:30 AM – 5:00 PM (Eastern).				
			</fo:block>

			<fo:block margin-top="2cm" font-weight="bold" text-align="center"
				font-size="18px">
				1-888-959-2786
			</fo:block>

			<fo:block margin-top="2cm" text-align="center" font-size="14px">
				Thank you for choosing
				<fo:inline font-weight="bold">Protexure Lawyers</fo:inline>
				.
			</fo:block>


		</fo:block-container>



	</xsl:template>
</xsl:stylesheet>
